==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fenestrate
<hw>Fe*nes"trate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fenestratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>fenestrare</ets> to furnish with
openings and windows.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having numerous openings;
irregularly reticulated; <as>as, <ex>fenestrate</ex> membranes;
<ex>fenestrate</ex> fronds.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having transparent spots, as the
wings of certain butterflies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fenestrated</ent>⟦br⟧
